race.comment: THEY'REALLSISTERS (8) had trialled coming into her campaign and hasn't disappointed. Her win last start over this trip was impressive and she maps perfectly for Pike. Can improve sharply again third-up here and she can claim the feature. MARIA LUCIA (9) sat on the speed and was far too good on debut, running away to win by 2L. Carries more weight here, but gets Chris Parnham in the saddle and sharp improvement wouldn't surprise. Can remain unbeaten. DARYTE (7) was very impressive on debut before jumping a $1.45 when behind MARIA LUCIA last time out. Needs some luck from out wide but meets that galloper better at the weights. Not to be discounted despite the wide alley. PROPERATA (3) trialled well going into his last start where he got back and never really featured. Drawn nicely here and can put his best foot forward. YAMANEX (13) was solid on debut and draws the inside with the visors on first time. Can make an impression.
